net.imglib2.cache.util

Interface KeyBimap<S,T>

  • Type Parameters:
    S - source type
    T - target type

    public interface KeyBimap<S,T>
    A bidirectional map between key types S and T (source and target). This is used to create adapters exposing a T→V cache as a S→V cache.

    The S→T mapping must be injective. If the S→T mapping is not bijective, getSource(Object) should return null for target keys with no corresponding source key.

    Author:
    Tobias Pietzsch
